    <item>
      <id>3</id>
      <text>Derivatives formed by substitution of the above parent ions by groups having two or three free valencies on the same atom. Such derivatives are, where possible, designated by a specific class name. E.g. RC≡O+ hydrocarbylidyne oxonium ions, R2C=N+H2X−iminium compounds, RC≡NH+nitrilium ions.</text>
